VERDICT: the gate is causally correct and tells us the TRUE answer — the payload was NEVER causally
dependent on the episode for these entities. Ablating 12 load-bearing lobster tokens moved the
payload LL by +0.01 because "a species of lobster found in the North Atlantic Ocean" is PARAMETRIC
knowledge: the 12B regenerates it from weights. The roof is held up by parametric steel, not the
episodic columns. The wiki facts are parametric, not episodic.

ROOT CAUSE (the campaign's terminal truth, now proven at the root): you cannot measure episodic
causal dependency on memories whose content the model ALREADY HAS parametrically. The corpus —
wiki passages about real entities the model knows — is the wall. The one genuinely-novel episode
(audio needle, where ablation WOULD collapse) has no tokens to target (empty mask = 0, the
"feature not bug"); the one wiki entity the model actually confabulates without memory (Boulter)
is the lost-provenance 84-tok ghost we could not re-mint. The thesis (causal ablation > empty-cache
baseline) is SOUND and the instrument is DURABLE — it just needs a NOVEL-needle corpus to fire.

